---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — Nostaliga"
  description="The terms for using the Nostaliga app and website."
  path="/terms"
>
  <article class="prose-nostaliga pt-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Terms of Use
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Last updated {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Nostaliga is built by Dinakar Tumu (contact: <a
        href="mailto:dinakartumu@gmail.com">dinakartumu@gmail.com</a
      >). These terms govern your use of the Nostaliga iOS and iPadOS apps and
      this website (together, "Nostaliga"). By using Nostaliga you agree to these
      terms. If you do not agree, please do not use it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">What Nostaliga is</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Nostaliga is a personal app that assembles a private timeline of your life
      from data you choose to connect or import — your music history, photos,
      workouts, check-ins, watches, calendar events, and your own social
      archives. It has no user accounts, and all correlation and display happen
      on your device. How your data is handled is described in our <a
        href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a
      >, which is part of these terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Your license to use Nostaliga</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Nostaliga grants you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable
      license to use the app for your own non-commercial use, subject to these
      terms and to the Apple Media Services / App Store Terms of Service that
      apply to any app you download from the App Store. You may not copy, modify,
      reverse-engineer, resell, or redistribute the app except as permitted by
      law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Third-party services and your accounts</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <li>
        Connecting a service (Spotify, Apple Music, Last.fm, Strava, Trakt,
        Swarm/Foursquare, Adobe Lightroom) or importing an archive (Twitter/X,
        Instagram, Facebook) is your choice. Your use of each service remains
        governed by that service's own terms and privacy policy.
      </li>
      <li>
        You are responsible for having the right to access and import the data
        you connect or upload, and for keeping your own third-party accounts
        secure.
      </li>
      <li>
        Nostaliga is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by any of
        these services. Their names and logos belong to their respective owners.
      </li>
      <li>
        Third-party services may change or discontinue their APIs or data
        exports at any time, which may affect what Nostaliga can show. That is
        outside our control.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Acceptable use</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Use Nostaliga only for lawful purposes and only with data you are entitled
      to use. Do not use it to infringe anyone's rights, to attempt to disrupt or
      probe the token-swap endpoints, or in any way that violates a connected
      service's terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">No warranty</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Nostaliga is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of any
      kind, whether express or implied, including fitness for a particular
      purpose and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the app will be
      uninterrupted, error-free, or that imported data will be complete or
      accurate. You are responsible for maintaining your own backups of any data
      that matters to you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, Nostaliga and its developer will
      not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
      punitive damages, or for any loss of data, arising out of or related to
      your use of (or inability to use) Nostaliga. Because Nostaliga is a free
      app, our total liability for any claim is limited to zero dollars.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Price</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Nostaliga is currently offered free of charge and contains no in-app
      purchases or subscriptions. If that changes, the applicable terms and
      pricing will be shown before any purchase.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      We may update these terms from time to time. The updated version will be
      posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of
      Nostaliga after a change means you accept the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:dinakartumu@gmail.com"
        >dinakartumu@gmail.com</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
